IRS990.MissionDesc: OUR MISSION IS TO PROVIDE MEDICAL, DENTAL & SUPPORTIVE SERVICES IN A REMOTE, RURAL AREA OF NORTHERN MINNESOTA. AS A FEDERALLY QUALIFIED HEALTH CENTER IN A REMOTE, RURAL AREA, IT IS OUR GOAL TO BE CUSTOMER FOCUSED WITHOUT REGARD TO ECONOMIC STATUS OR ANY OTHER ARTIFICIAL BARRIER. WE INTEND TO PROVIDE QUALITY PRIMARY CARE THAT MEETS THE NEEDS OF PEOPLE IN OUR DESIGNATED SERVICE AREA THROUGH COLLABORATIVE EFFORTS WITH CRITICAL ACCESS HOSPITALS, CARE CENTERS, SPECIALISTS, ASSOCIATIONS, FOUNDATIONS AND OTHER APPROPRIATE OR AVAILABLE OPPORTUNITIES. OUR CORE VALUE IS THE CARE OF FAMILIES, FRIENDS AND VISITORS WHO RESIDE IN OR TRAVEL THROUGH OUR REGION BY ASSISTING TO IMPROVE THEIR HEALTH. THIS CARE IS PROVIDED AT OUR MEDICAL CLINICS IN BIGFORK, BIG FALLS, COOK, FLOODWOOD,NORTHOME, AND TOWER MN AND AT OUR DENTAL CLINICS IN COOK, FLOODWOOD, AND TOWER, MN. CARE IS ALSO PROVIDED THROUGH CONTRACTS WITH BIGFORK VALLEY AND COOK HOSPITALS AND THEIR ASSOCIATED NURSING HOMES AS WELL AS AT NORTHOME CARE

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS UPON RECEIPT FROM THE PREPARER. THE COPY WAS INCLUDED WITH THE STANDARD MATERIALS (MEETING MINUTES, FINANCIAL REPORTS, ETC.) PROVIDED TO THE BOARD PRIOR TO THEIR MONTHLY MEETING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CAHS REQUIRES ANNUAL REPORTING FROM ALL DIRECTORS AND KEY EMPLOYEES REGARDING ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST WITH RELATED ORGANIZATIONS AND VENDORS WITH WHOM THE ORGANIZATION TRANSACTS BUSINESS. CAHS MONITORS DISCLOSURES PROVIDED TO ANY AFFIRMATIVE REPONSES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD'S FINANCE COMMITTEE CONDUCTS AN ANNUAL COMPENSATION REVIEW OF CAHS KEY EMPLOYEES USING SALARY SURVEYS FROM THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS, THE MN DEPT. OF EMPLOYMENT AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT, AND OTHER AVAILABLE SALARY SURVEYS. THE COMMITTEE DOCUMENTS EACH EMPLOYEE'S COMPENSATION RELATIVE TO SURVEY DATA AND SUBSTANTIATES REASONS FOR SUBSTANTIAL VARIANCES FROM AVAILABLE DATA.
